      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">What do relocators from London and the South East ask about Cheshire prices?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 28px 0;">London averages £551,294 (ONS, Dec 2025). Cheshire averages £314,000. Relocators from southern England gain 45-60% more floor space per pound in Northwich (£242,657), Chester (£205,000-£340,000), and Frodsham (£255,000) compared to equivalent London budgets (Rightmove, 2025).</p>
