        {[
          { initials: 'RB', name: 'R.B.', location: 'Moving from Surrey', question: "We have a budget of £550,000. In Surrey that buys a tired three-bed semi. What does the same money get in Cheshire?", answer: "In Knutsford (£606,876 average), £550,000 reaches a four-bedroom semi-detached or a modest detached on a quieter street. In Northwich (£242,657 average), £550,000 buys a new-build five-bedroom detached with garden and double garage. In Macclesfield or Chester Newton and Hoole, the same budget reaches a large detached four-bedroom. In Wilmslow (£489,105 average), £550,000 reaches a three-bedroom semi or a two-bedroom apartment in a premium location.", colour: '#3D5A3E' },
