      <div style="border-left: 3px solid #3D5A3E; background-color: rgba(61, 90, 62, 0.04); padding: 24px 28px;">
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: #3D5A3E; margin: 0 0 8px 0; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em;">Good to know</p>
        <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #444444; margin: 0;">
          Cheshire house price data on this page combines three sources with different methodologies. ONS UK HPI (December 2025) uses Land Registry completed transactions and reports authority-level averages. Rightmove (12 months to February 2026) uses asking prices and recent sold prices for town-level breakdowns. CW&C Council ward data (2023) uses Land Registry median prices at ward level. ONS figures lag by 2-3 months due to registration delays. Rightmove asking prices run 3-5% above completed transaction prices. Cheshire has 34% detached housing stock versus 22% nationally (Census 2021), which inflates the county average relative to areas with more terraced and flat stock.
        </p>
